<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-04-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-04-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="37" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d37">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.0021/94a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Legation at Brussels</gloss>
                            </hi><note n="2" xml:id="d37fn2">Sent also to the Embassies at Rio de
                                Janeiro, Vienna, and Madrid, and the Legations at Peking,
                                Copenhagen, Athens, The Hague, Christiania, and Bucharest.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Circular telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-01">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 1, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Endeavor obtain early reply to representations made in accordance with
                            Department’s instruction May 29, 1915, regarding Seamen’s Act, approved
                            March 4, 1915.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>